name: Abrade
oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Abrade deals 3 damage to target creature.
• Destroy target artifact.
flavor_text: The desert is a voracious beast, devouring both flesh and stone.

name: Ancestral Blade
oracle_text:
When Ancestral Blade enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 white Soldier creature token, then attach Ancestral Blade to it.
Equipped creature gets +1/+1.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

name: Broken Wings
oracle_text: Destroy target artifact, enchantment, or creature with flying.
flavor_text:
"Fynn climbed the highest peak and waited, still and silent, until the falling snow had hidden him entirely. When the great eagle flew past, the hunter's aim was true."
—Saga of the Wisdom Seeker

name: Bushmeat Poacher
oracle_text: {1}, {T}, Sacrifice another creature: You gain life equal to the sacrificed creature's toughness. Draw a card.
flavor_text: "If you've never feasted on Zagoth terror-pig, I got the best price you'll find."

name: Doom Blade
oracle_text: Destroy target nonblack creature.
flavor_text:
"An angel can shine like the sun, inspire the weak, and even threaten victory over darkness. But in the end it matters not, for it still dies like any other pest."
—Ob Nixilis

name: Doomed Dissenter
oracle_text: When Doomed Dissenter dies, create a 2/2 black Zombie creature token.
flavor_text: There is only one fate left to those banished from the God-Pharaoh's city.

name: Dragon Egg
oracle_text:
Defender
When Dragon Egg dies, create a 2/2 red Dragon creature token with flying and "{R}: This creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn."
flavor_text: Dragon birth lairs are littered with treasure to entice the young from their eggs.

name: Dragon Hatchling
oracle_text:
Flying
{R}: Dragon Hatchling gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor_text:
"Those dragons grow fast. For a while they feed on squirrels and goblins and then suddenly you're missing a mammoth."
—Hurdek, Mazar mammoth trainer

name: Dusk Legion Zealot
oracle_text: When Dusk Legion Zealot enters the battlefield, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor_text: Once they reached Orazca, the Legion's explorers ransacked tombs and temples, hunting for the Immortal Sun.

name: Elvish Rejuvenator
oracle_text: When Elvish Rejuvenator enters the battlefield, look at the top five cards of your library. You may put a land card from among them onto the battlefield tapped. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.

name: Elvish Skysweeper
oracle_text: {4}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Destroy target creature with flying.
flavor_text: The spires of Ravnica are no different from the tall trees of other planes. The elves navigate and protect them just the same.

name: Elvish Visionary
oracle_text: When Elvish Visionary enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor_text: "From a tiny sprout, the greatest trees grow and flourish. May the seeds of your mind be equally fruitful."

name: Fleshbag Marauder
oracle_text: When Fleshbag Marauder enters the battlefield, each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor_text: Grixis is a world where the only things found in abundance are death and decay. Corpses, whole or in part, are the standard currency among necromancers and demons.

name: Gavony Unhallowed
oracle_text: Whenever another creature you control dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Gavony Unhallowed.
flavor_text:
"We entered the church in search of solace, but it became clear we wouldn't find it there."
—Grete, Order of Saint Traft

name: Goblin Motivator
oracle_text: {T}: Target creature gains haste until end of turn. (It can attack and {T} this turn.)
flavor_text: Small words stoke large flames.

name: Howling Golem
oracle_text: Whenever Howling Golem attacks or blocks, each player draws a card.
flavor_text: It wails of buried riches and the souls lost seeking them.

name: Impulse
oracle_text: Look at the top four cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.
flavor_text: "You call it luck. I call it preparation."

name: Jeering Homunculus
oracle_text: When Jeering Homunculus enters the battlefield, you may goad target creature. (Until your next turn, that creature attacks each combat if able and attacks a player other than you if able.)
flavor_text: Mklthd had always hated crowds . . . and they had always hated him.

name: Joraga Visionary
oracle_text: When Joraga Visionary enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor_text: "If you only follow where the paths lead, you merely go where others have gone before you."

name: Kargan Dragonrider
oracle_text: As long as you control a Dragon, Kargan Dragonrider has flying. (It can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor_text: "Only those who give the dragons the respect they deserve may bear our title."

name: Kitesail Apprentice
oracle_text: As long as Kitesail Apprentice is equipped, it gets +1/+1 and has flying.
flavor_text: Carving lines through the sky, kite sailors map trails for the pilgrims below to follow.

name: Kor Outfitter
oracle_text: When Kor Outfitter enters the battlefield, you may attach target Equipment you control to target creature you control.
flavor_text: "We take only what we need to survive. Believe me, you will need this."

name: Llanowar Elves
oracle_text: {T}: Add {G}.
flavor_text: As patient and generous as life, as harsh and merciless as nature.

name: Maalfeld Twins
oracle_text: When Maalfeld Twins dies, create two 2/2 black Zombie creature tokens.
flavor_text:
"Who am I to break up a family?"
—Gisa the Mad

name: Mana Geyser
oracle_text: Add {R} for each tapped land your opponents control.
flavor_text: The Quicksilver Sea hissed and bubbled at the indignity. The Vulshok shaman just smiled.

name: Pilgrim of the Ages
oracle_text:
When Pilgrim of the Ages enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic Plains card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
{6}: Return Pilgrim of the Ages from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Rabid Bite
oracle_text: Target creature you control deals damage equal to its power to target creature you don't control.
flavor_text: A healthy felidar is voracious yet regal. A rabid felidar is nothing more than appetite lashed to frothing jaws.

name: Ram Through
oracle_text: Target creature you control deals damage equal to its power to target creature you don't control. If the creature you control has trample, excess damage is dealt to that creature's controller instead.
flavor_text:
"Need a medic! And some stonemasons!"
—Wyllon, Drannith merchant

name: Rapacious Dragon
oracle_text:
Flying
When Rapacious Dragon enters the battlefield, create two Treasure tokens. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
flavor_text:
"Surely it won't notice if I take—"
—Theria the Sly, last words

name: Repulse
oracle_text:
Return target creature to its owner's hand.
Draw a card.
flavor_text: "You aren't invited."

name: Run Away Together
oracle_text: Choose two target creatures controlled by different players. Return those creatures to their owners' hands.
flavor_text:
"Virtue is virtue, whatever the heart that nurtures it."
—Malacan, Vantress exile

name: Sea Gate Oracle
oracle_text: When Sea Gate Oracle enters the battlefield, look at the top two cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the other on the bottom of your library.
flavor_text: "The secret entrance should be near."

name: Seize the Spoils
oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card.
Draw two cards and create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
flavor_text: "Grab what you want and burn the rest. Leave nothing behind."

name: Sign in Blood
oracle_text: Target player draws two cards and loses 2 life.
flavor_text:
"It's always my brightest students who make the worst decisions."
—Shaile, Silverquill dean

name: Strength of Arms
oracle_text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. If you control an Equipment, create a 1/1 white Human Soldier creature token.
flavor_text:
"We fight not for Avacyn, but for her ideals; not for the church, but for its people."
—Thalia, Guardian of Thraben

name: Supernatural Stamina
oracle_text: Until end of turn, target creature gets +2/+0 and gains "When this creature dies, return it to the battlefield tapped under its owner's control."
flavor_text:
"All are not equal—neither in life nor after death. Bontu's favorites will stand highest in eternity."
—Senifet, vizier of Bontu

name: Taunting Elf
oracle_text: All creatures able to block Taunting Elf do so.
flavor_text: The safety of the village depends on the beast thinking with its stomach.

name: Thornweald Archer
oracle_text: Reach, deathtouch
flavor_text: Their arrows are tipped with basilisk eyes and fletched with cockatrice feathers.

name: Village Rites
oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Draw two cards.
flavor_text: The Skelle raise scorn poles in conquered villages—cursed totems of wood and bone that sap survivors of physical strength and the will to fight back.

name: Wirewood Pride
oracle_text: Target creature gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the number of Elves on the battlefield.
flavor_text: "Though you may leave this haven we have found, may our strength never leave you."
